1. Npm init (-y) to initlize the node enviroment after this the package.json file is created.
2. The package.json file is refring to the complete detail about the project.
3. Install express package by command (npm i express) after this the complete required folder and files will be occur in the revision folder.
4. Install nodemon for restarting the server. 
5. Install ejs (Embeded Javascript) by (npm i ejs).
6. Configure the package.json file with start script or command.

Configure the ejs package
1. Make views folder in parent directory.
2. Create your ejs files with the extension called .ejs.